-- Argentine Stocks: Galicia, Siderar Fall; Ledesma Advances
-- B y   C a m i l a   R u s s o
-- 2012-01-11T15:37:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-11/argentine-stocks-galicia-siderar-fall-ledesma-advances.html
The following companies are having
unusual price changes in Argentine trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and share prices are as of 12:12 p.m. in  Buenos
Aires .  The  Merval (MERVAL)  Index fell 0.2 percent to 2,828.16.  Ledesma SAAI (LEDE)  (LEDE AF) advanced 1.4 percent to 7.02 pesos.
The Argentine sugar producer rose after saying in a filing to
the Buenos Aires stock exchange that it will distribute
dividends worth 34 million pesos ($7.9 million), or 0.08 pesos
per share, starting Jan. 18.  Shares of financial and industrial companies fell on
concern that the global economic expansion is weakening after
the European Union cut euro-area growth to 0.1 percent in the
third quarter from 0.2 percent estimated earlier.  Grupo Financiero Galicia SA (GGAL)  (GGAL AF), Argentina’s largest
consumer lender, dropped 1.4 percent to 3.60 pesos.  Siderar SAIC (ERAR)  (ERAR AF),  Argentina ’s largest steel producer,
declined 0.2 percent to 25.70 pesos.  To contact the reporters on this story:
Camila Russo in Buenos Aires at 
 crusso15@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
